The paper presents a new memory augmented neural network model for multi-view learning with sequential data. The model uses two neural encoders for reading from and writing to two external memories, which capture intra-view interactions and long-term dependencies. The paper also demonstrates the model's effectiveness on various experiments, including drug prescription and disease progressions in healthcare, which suggests that the paper could be categorized under several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
